<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-1263] Serialise/Deserialise Lambda value for OnlineLogisticRegression </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-1263</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The value for Lambda in OnlineLogisticRegression seems not the be serialised/deserialised correctly. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If I train a model with a specific lambda value, serialise it, then read it back in, the value of Lambda goes back to the default value (1.0e-5). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve created a patch that adds the lambda value into the write/readFields (org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable). Patch includes a unit test that checks the values after serialising/deserialising to/from a ByteArray. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think this is correct, unless I&apos;m missing something obvious?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note: this patch is not backwards compatible - can easily adapt to be more backwards compatible if required. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
